print("="*70)

summary = """
✅ CLASS: A blueprint for creating objects
   • Defines attributes (characteristics)
   • Defines methods (actions/behaviors)

✅ OBJECT/INSTANCE: A real copy of a class
   • Created using the __init__ constructor
   • Has its own values for attributes

✅ ATTRIBUTE: A variable that belongs to the class
   • Store data about the object
   • Accessed using self.attribute

✅ METHOD: A function that belongs to the class
   • Performs actions on the object
   • First parameter is always "self"

✅ CONSTRUCTOR (__init__): Special method
   • Called automatically when creating an object
   • Initializes the attributes

✅ ENCAPSULATION: Protect private data
   • Use __ before the attribute to make it private
   • Example: self.__balance (don't access directly)

✅ INHERITANCE: A class inherits from another
   • PARENT class: contains common characteristics
   • CHILD class: inherits and adds its own characteristics
   • Use super().__init__() to call the PARENT constructor

✅ METHOD OVERRIDING: Redefine a PARENT class method
   • The CHILD class can modify the behavior
   • Example: Dog inherits from Animal but make_sound() is different
"""

print(summary)


